cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, math.OC 

This paper is about the mathematical foundations of deep learning, specifically the matrix calculus needed to understand the training of deep neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and math.OC (Optimization and Control).
